<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-971-916  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 971 916.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer-Aided Design  Nov 1989 v21 n9 p561(9).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Design of an automated assembly environment. (technical)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Roy, U.; Banerjee, P.; Liu, C.R.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A design environment for acquisition, analysis and validation ofinformation for automated mechanical assembly is proposed in thispaper.andP;  The environment acts as a preprocessing step before theactual assembly operation.andP;  The working memory - consisting mainlyof instances of component and subassembly data objects and a B-repbased structured face adjacency graph - is used to establish theassembly precedence relationship.andP;  The environment has beenimplemented in the object-oriented programming languageSmalltalk-80.andP;  An object-based approach has been preferred to aprocedural language because of increased modularity, dataabstraction, and efficiency of the code.andP;  The hierarchical class(data type) structure of object-oriented programming has been usedto define a hierarchical mating requirement module permittingknowledge inheritance from parent classes.andP;  (Reprinted bypermission of the publisher.)andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     CAD-CAMObject-Oriented ProgrammingData RepresentationTheoretical ResearchAssembly LineNew TechniqueMechanical EngineeringComputer-Aided EngineeringModeling.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   Virtual functional relationship. (chart)Composite functional relationship. (chart)Vice assembly. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>